ing' in order to assess how the Beckett oeuvre can help us rethink contemporary preoccupations with materialism, neurology, sculpture, music and television. The volume is a scholarly intervention in the fields of Beckett studies which offers its chapters as case studies to use in the classroom. It will prove of interest to advanced students and scholars in English, French, Comparative Literature, Drama, Visual Studies, Philosophy, Music, Cinema and TV studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aBeckett&apos.  aDoris Salcedo.  aHuman Wishes.  aJean-Paul Sartre.  aMorton Feldman.  aSamuel Beckett.  amusicalisation.  anothingness.  aparadoxical fidelity.  as cinema.  as television plays.  atelevisual production history.1 aBignell, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoxall, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrater, Enoch, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaselli, Daniela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaselli, Daniela, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDolar, Mladen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEagleton, Terry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelberts, Matthijs, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaws, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPilling, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aProsser, Bill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.l